meta {
  name: Test Bad Content-Type
  type: http
  seq: 14
}

post {
  url: http://localhost:30080/example-api/data
  body: text
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/x-evil-payload
}

body:text {
  {"test": "data"}
}

docs {
  # Test Content-Type Enforcement (WAF)

  Sends a POST request with a disallowed Content-Type header.
  The WAF should **block** this with a **403 Forbidden** response.

  ## Prerequisites
  1. Deploy a service (e.g., "example-api")
  2. Go to the service's **Firewall** tab in the UI
  3. Turn ON the **Header Sanitization** toggle

  ## Expected Response (WAF enabled)
  ```json
  {
    "detail": "Request blocked by WAF",
    "reason": "Disallowed Content-Type: application/x-evil-payload",
    "attack_type": "headers",
    "pattern": "Content-Type enforcement"
  }
  ```

  ## Allowed Content-Types
  - application/json
  - application/x-www-form-urlencoded
  - multipart/form-data
  - text/plain
  - application/xml / text/xml
  - application/octet-stream
}
